2 âOrgan Clearanceâ

Given the following scheme:

The blood flow into this organ is 1000 ml/min (Qin). A constant concentration of 5 mg/liter enters the organ (Cin). The sole mechanism of elimination by this organ is metabolism, and, in a one hour period at steady state, the organ metabolizes 90 milligrams of the drug. The blood flow rates into and out of the organ are equal. The volume of distribution of this drug is 75 liters.

  1. What is the extraction ratio of this eliminating organ?
# Your answer here
  1. What is the steady state concentration leaving the organ to return to the blood pool? (i.e., Cout)
# Your answer here
  1. Calculate the organ clearance. Given that this organ clearance represents the only means of elimination from the body, calculate the half-life.
# Your answer here
  1. What would be the rate of metabolism if the concentration entering the organ was 25 mg/liter?
# Your answer here
  1. Calculate the change in organ clearance when the volume of distribution of the drug doubles to 150 liters.
# Your answer here

# Your answer here

    1. the rate of metabolism when 500 mg of the drug has been eliminated (under normal liver function).
# Your answer here
